When I add a meeting notes, or a page, and reference Actions to other users (using @), they as a user see the action in their list, but they are not able to tick the action.

Would be good for setting group permissions for a workspace to have a tick box that says, those assigned in a task can mark task completed.

At the moment the workaround would be to add write permissions per meeting minutes for those who attended the meeting, which is not a usable solution for frequent meeting minutes / action assignations.

