Many Chrome for Mac users are familiar with Cmd-1 through Cmd-0 as a way to quickly switch between multiple tabs. However, when editing a wiki page on Confluence, these keyboard shortcuts are overridden to apply different formatting rules. (This is grief-inducing.)

After accidentally hitting Cmd-1 and applying the wrong formatting to a newly-typed line of text, if I press Cmd-Z to undo that formatting change, it will actually undo the text entry. So I then have to either manually adjust the formatting myself or retype the line. (This is immensely frustrating, even more so than the Cmd-1 override itself.)

According to your priority definitions this is "minor", but it's such an annoyance that it makes me really _hate_ editing Confluence pages, even though I love the rest of the software.

